OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F304A1771956278
OL,3,CWomb transplants: How do they work and
OL,4,Cwill they become more common?
OL,6,FWhile women with a transplanted womb
OL,7,Fcan have other babies, the
OL,8,Ftransplanted womb does need to be
OL,9,Fremoved afterwards, otherwise the
OL,10,Fmother would have to use
OL,11,Fimmunosuppressant drugs for the rest
OL,12,Fof their lives to prevent the body
OL,13,Ffrom recognising the new organ as a
OL,14,Fforeign organ and attacking it.
OL,16,FContinuing to use immunosuppressant
OL,17,Fdrugs for a sustained period carries
OL,18,Flong-term risks because they weaken
OL,19,Fthe immune system.
OL,21,FAre womb transplants dangerous?
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/14
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
