OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F304A1771956278
OL,3,CWomb transplants: How do they work and
OL,4,Cwill they become more common?
OL,6,FA further 1,000 women lose their wombs
OL,7,Feach year as a result of
OL,8,Fhysterectomies, the medical procedure
OL,9,Fof removing the uterus, often when
OL,10,Ftreating women with cervical and
OL,11,Futerine cancers, according to data
OL,12,Fpublished by Womb Transplant UK.
OL,14,FMayer-Rokitansky-Kuster-Hauser (MRKH)
OL,15,Fis an example of a condition that may
OL,16,Fcause women to need a womb transplant
OL,17,F- it is a congenital disorder that
OL,18,Fmeans the womb is underdeveloped or
OL,19,Fnot present at all.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G7/14
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
