OL,3,CWomb transplants: How do they work and
OL,4,Cwill they become more common?
OL,6,FIn the UK, two babies have been born,
OL,7,Fand three transplant patients have not
OL,8,Fhad a baby yet, but are undergoing
OL,9,Fprivate IVF.
OL,11,FWhat is the history behind the UK's
OL,12,Fsuccessful womb transplants?
OL,14,FThe first living baby born following a
OL,15,Fwomb transplantation happened in
OL,16,FSweden in 2014. A 35-year-old woman
OL,17,Fwith MRKH received the donor womb from
OL,18,Fa living 61-year-old.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G11/14
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
