OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F304A1771956278
OL,3,CWomb transplants: How do they work and
OL,4,Cwill they become more common?
OL,6,FThe births in the UK come after 25
OL,7,Fyears of womb transplant research, and
OL,8,Fthat research had already led to the
OL,9,Fdevelopment of other surgical
OL,10,Fprocedures.
OL,12,FThe abdominal radical trachelectomy -
OL,13,Fwhich enables fertility preservation
OL,14,Fof many thousands of women with early-
OL,15,Fstage cervical cancer - and the
OL,16,Fmodified Strassman Procedure, which
OL,17,Fhas been used to preserve the
OL,18,Freproductive potential of women with
OL,19,Fplacental site tumours, have both been
OL,20,Fdeveloped as a result of womb
OL,21,Ftransplant research.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G12/14
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
